[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/reverse_drury"]
[Student "S"]
{You like partner's \H suit but you have very little defensive strength. This is a good hand to preempt the bidding, trying to keep them from finding a \S fit.

So you jump to 3\H. Partner realizes you don't have any strength since you did not invoke Reverse Drury. He passes and you have bought the contract. It appears that their side might be able to make 4\S.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "2"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "W:T642.KQ5.86.AQ93 K3.JT863.T74.KJ2 QJ9875.A4.KQJ.87 A.972.A9532.T654"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "W"]
pass pass 1S pass 2C pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "47df23cffd0168b3a6b8b9fbff69a27b3ac067f575019d208a03e6ed8b807a84"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/reverse_drury"]
[Student "S"]
{You open in third seat and the bidding continues as shown.  

Partner has a limit raise in \Ss and wonders if you have a full strength opening bid. Your 15 point hand is enough to insist on game, but opposite a passed hand you have no interest in a slam.

So you sign-off at 4\S.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "N:QJ96.AK.852.9765 75.Q986.KQ93.T83 KT843.J53.J76.AK A2.T742.AT4.QJ42"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "2S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
pass pass 1S pass 2C pass 2D pass 2S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "4edfd4dc50700942e7fcc87afa5f74e0c46a557e105041dae6cb9460d71fbb8d"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/reverse_drury"]
[Student "S"]
{With 11 points in support of \Ss you need to let partner know. The way to do it is to bid 2\C.

Partner rebids 2\D, confirming a full-strength opening bid.  

You've told partner you had at least a limit raise, now you need to tell him that it is pretty minimal. You bid 2\S and everybody passes.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "E:JT96.Q8.86.K8653 42.A962.AT42.Q94 KQ875.K74.KQ7.T2 A3.JT53.J953.AJ7"]
[Declarer "W"]
[Contract "3S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
pass pass 1S pass 3S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 2, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
