[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/reverse_drury"]
[Student "S"]
{You open in third seat and the bidding continues as shown.  

If you thought East had 11 points you'd bid 4\S. But you know he has a weak hand - with 10+ points and support he would have said 2\C.

His 3\S bid is just preemptive, so you pass.}

